{
  "stem": "9943.5",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I left Moscow on the second plane that left Moscow as this translator, not as a doctor, because that's what the man that was in charge of the newspaper that was [? followed ?] in Poland needed a translator and [? decide ?] [? for there ?] I have acquaintances.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I had acquaintances that wanted to-- to help me get out of the Soviet Union because I thought they wouldn't let me out.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Everybody still asks, me how they did you leave?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was a war of '44.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In '44, I came to Lublin.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In Lublin, I was exactly at the time when they did free Majdanek, that [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Camp Majdanek.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I don't know whether you know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Sure.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I interviewed them, those who had left Majdanek at that time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Nine children were among them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I interviewed those kids.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So that-- that I am already in Poland.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] from Lublin, in a couple of weeks, I was sitting by myself in the radio, and I was the writing down how the Russian, what did they conquer, every single village, and so on, how they were making progress to-- on the front line.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then, you know, was this Polish Warsaw Uprising thing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And pretty soon, after a couple of weeks that I functioned as that [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] translator, I went to Lodz, where I got my job as a senior assistant at the university clinic, and in neurology I was working.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In the meantime, from Paris came [INAUDIBLE], who was a husband of a friend of mine with whom I shared a-- a room in-- in-- in Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She was married to him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I knew them from Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they used to bring French people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
